  "computational_details": [],
  "unmapped_findings": [
    "Reduction of area (RA) values from tensile tests: AL 22.2%, AT 26.8%, BL 22.7%, BT 27.2%, CL 24.2%, CT 19.4%.",
    "For alloy B, the fatigue S-N curve points (reverse bending) are: 10^5 cycles at 420 MPa, 10^6 cycles at 320 MPa, 10^7 cycles at 230 MPa. BL shows better fatigue resistance than BT.",
    "For alloys A and C, the fatigue S-N curves of longitudinal and transverse specimens coincide, indicating no orientation dependence of fatigue properties.",
    "The ferrite phase in alloy B is described as fine and soft; a blunting effect at the initial stage of fatigue and intense work hardening at the later stage may contribute to crack arrest when ferrite string is perpendicular to crack propagation."
  ]
